Visited Bijou for a refined dining experience, and it truly delivered on both flavour and presentation. From start to finish, the meal showcased high-quality ingredients, thoughtful execution, and a touch of elegance that sets it apart.

We began with the samosa chaat, which struck a perfect balance between crisp textures and layered flavours â vibrant, tangy, and satisfying. The lamb chops were beautifully cooked â tender, well-marinated, and full of depth. Served alongside rustic chips that were golden and crisp, they made for an impressive start.

The bao buns were soft and generously filled with salmon, offering a lovely contrast of texture and flavour. The Mongolian beef with noodles stood out with its bold, savoury glaze â rich, slightly sweet, and incredibly moreish.

One of the highlights was the Lamb Luscious â a slow-cooked lamb curry that was rich and comforting, paired with perfectly cooked egg fried rice that soaked up every bit of flavour.

For dessert, the sticky toffee pudding served with a Magnum ice cream bar was indulgent and warm, while the Lotus New York cheesecake with vanilla ice cream offered a smooth, creamy finish to the meal.

The ambience at Bijou complements the food â elegant yet welcoming, making it an excellent choice for both intimate dinners and special occasions. Itâs clear this is a restaurant that pays close attention to detail â from flavour profiles to plating â and one that stands a level above typical alternatives in the halal dining space. Bibimbop offers a concise yet diverse menu that delivers exceptional quality and unbelievable flavours. This spot has quickly become one of my favourite meals of the year, thanks to its bold Korean fusion and attention to detail in every dish.

The menu features carefully curated options that focus on freshness and quality ingredients, ensuring every bite is packed with flavour. I had the pleasure of trying several dishes, and each one was outstanding, but the beef brisket deserves a special mention as the standout meat choiceâperfectly tender and rich in taste.

For those looking to try a bit of everything, Iâd specifically recommend Meal Deal 4 as the perfect munch box for one. Itâs ideal for satisfying your cravings, offering a mix of cheeky kimchi fries, buffalo wings, a bao bun of your choice, a mini corn dog, and a drink. This combo gives you a taste of the best Bibimbop has to offer, all in one satisfying box.

Speaking of the corn dog, it was an absolute delight! Crispy on the outside, wonderfully cheesy on the inside, and with a satisfying cheese pull that made it a real standout. Itâs a must-try for anyone who loves a perfect combination of crunch and gooey cheese.

The Bibimbap bowls, with their vibrant mix of fresh vegetables, sauces, and protein options, are another must-try. Pair them with sides like Kimchi Fries, topped with spicy mayo and Korean chilli flakes, or Buffalo Wings, which are bursting with Korean-inspired flavours. The Double Bao Buns were equally impressive, offering soft, fluffy buns with juicy fillings.

Whether youâre a fan of traditional Korean dishes or looking for a creative fusion twist, Bibimbop excels in both areas. The flavours, quality, and execution make it a place I highly recommend. Donât miss out on the brisket and the corn dogâtheyâre game-changers!
